  "title": "Village Historic District - Grand Canyon National Park (U.S. National Park Service)",
  "html": "<body class=\"ParkSite\"><span aria-label=\"Top of page\" id=\"__topdoc__\" role=\"navigation\"></span>\n\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n<div id=\"beforeSkipLinks\" tabindex=\"-1\"></div>\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n<div class=\"GlobalHeader usaGlobalHeader\" role=\"banner\">\n\n</div>\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<div aria-hidden=\"true\" aria-labelledby=\"exitModalLabel\" class=\"modal refreshableModal\" id=\"myModal\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n<div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n<div class=\"modal-content\">\n<div class=\"modal-header\">\n<h2 class=\"modal-title visually-hidden\" id=\"exitModalLabel\">Exiting nps.gov</h2>\n<button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"btn-close\" data-bs-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"></button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"modal-body\"></div>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Schedule\" id=\"cs_control_481716\"><div id=\"CS_Element_BannerContainer\" title=\"\"><div class=\"cs_GridRow\" id=\"gridRow_1_1_481716\"><div class=\"cs_GridColumn\" id=\"gridCol_1_1_1_1_481716\"><div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_CustomCF\" id=\"cs_control_828672\"><div id=\"CS_CCF_6265783_828672\">\n\n</div></div><div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_CustomCF\" id=\"cs_control_481828\"><div id=\"CS_CCF_6265783_481828\"> </div></div></div></div></div></div>\n<div id=\"Park-header\">\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"pull-left\">\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n\n</div>\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div aria-label=\"Alerts Notification\" class=\"AlertsNotification\" data-site-code=\"grca\" id=\"AlertsNotification\" role=\"dialog\">\n<div aria-live=\"polite\" class=\"AlertsNotification__Status visually-hidden\" role=\"status\">Loading alerts</div>\n<div class=\"collapse\">\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__Panel\">\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__Header\">\n<h2 class=\"Tag\" id=\"AlertsNotificationHeading\">Alerts In Effect</h2>\n<button aria-label=\"Dismiss\" class=\"AlertsNotification__DismissButton\" type=\"button\">\nDismiss\n<svg class=\"usa-icon\" focusable=\"false\" role=\"presentation\">\n<use href=\"/theme/assets/vendor/npsds/packages/icons/dist/sprite.svg#close\"></use>\n</svg>\n</button>\n<span class=\"hr clearfix\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__Body\" id=\"AlertsNotificationBody\">\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__MoreLinkContainer\">\n<svg class=\"usa-icon\" focusable=\"false\" role=\"presentation\">\n<use href=\"/theme/assets/vendor/npsds/packages/icons/dist/sprite.svg#add\"></use>\n</svg>\n<a class=\"AlertsNotification__MoreLink\" href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/conditions.htm\" id=\"AlertsNotificationMoreLink\" tabindex=\"-1\">\nmore information on current conditions...\n</a>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"MainContent\" id=\"main\" role=\"main\">\n\n<div aria-labelledby=\"modal-contact-us-label\" class=\"modal fade\" id=\"modal-contact-us\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n<div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n<div class=\"modal-content\">\n<div class=\"modal-header\">\n<h4 class=\"modal-title visually-hidden\" id=\"modal-contact-us-label\">Contact Us</h4>\n<button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"btn-close\" data-bs-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"></button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"modal-body\">\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"adminTools\"></div>\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"ColumnGrid row\">\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n<div class=\"container\">\n\n</div>\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<div class=\"ColumnMain col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"ContentHeader text-content-size\">\n<h1 class=\"page-title\">Village Historic District</h1>\n</div>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Layout\" id=\"cs_control_2\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"CS_Layout_Table\" id=\"cs_idLayout2\" summary=\"\" width=\"100%\"><tr class=\"CS_Layout_TR\"><td class=\"CS_Layout_TD\" id=\"cs_idCell2x1x1\">\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_6265832\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<p>On September 17, 1901, the First Steam-Powered Train, a spur line of the Santa Fe Railway, arrived to the South Rim of the Grand Canyon. With the arrival of the train, the quiet area of the South Rim rapidly expanded into the bustling Grand Canyon Village.<br/>\n<br/>\nThe first decade of the Santa Fe Railway’s arrival saw the construction of the luxurious, El Tovar, and shops, such as Hopi House and Verkamp’s Curios (today’s Verkamp’s Visitor Center). Over the next three decades, the Grand Canyon Village expanded to accommodate its growing visitation. Today visitors can take a step back in time and wander through this historically preserved village dating back to the early 1900s.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_7006257\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_7006257\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<h2>Historic Buildings in the Village</h2>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_6266681\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_6266681\">\n<div class=\"Component FeatureGrid\">\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-6\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -medium\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"http://grcahistory.org/sites/south-rim/verkamps/\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, 'http://grcahistory.org/sites/south-rim/verkamps/', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"A dark brown building with a National Park Service arrowhead on it.\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 640px, (min-width: 1200px) 550px, (min-width: 576px) 50vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/4C492B9F-AB1D-C009-BF4EA3AD69301896.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/4C492B9F-AB1D-C009-BF4EA3AD69301896.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/4C492B9F-AB1D-C009-BF4EA3AD69301896.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Verkamp's Visitor Center History</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">A curio shop and family home for more than a century, Verkamp's was the oldest family-owned concessioner in Grand Canyon.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-6\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -medium\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/colter_hopih_photos.htm\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, '/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/colter_hopih_photos.htm', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"A adobe pueblo building with two signs in the front.\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 640px, (min-width: 1200px) 550px, (min-width: 576px) 50vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/4C7574F6-D736-0BA3-B1381C13A9164064.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/4C7574F6-D736-0BA3-B1381C13A9164064.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/4C7574F6-D736-0BA3-B1381C13A9164064.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Hopi House History</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">The Hopi House pays tribute to the Hopi and their ancestors that have inhabited the Grand Canyon for centuries. </p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"http://grcahistory.org/sites/south-rim/grand-canyon-railway-depot/\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, 'http://grcahistory.org/sites/south-rim/grand-canyon-railway-depot/', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"A wooden railway depot next to a set of railroad tracks.\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/8A0580AD-C43A-57CD-047C39C14B173D96.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/8A0580AD-C43A-57CD-047C39C14B173D96.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/8A0580AD-C43A-57CD-047C39C14B173D96.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">The Grand Canyon Railway Depot History</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">The Grand Canyon Railway Depot is one of the oldest standing wooden train depots in the United States.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"http://grcahistory.org/sites/south-rim/el-tovar/\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, 'http://grcahistory.org/sites/south-rim/el-tovar/', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"A wooden Swiss chalet lodge. \" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/8A414172-E3E8-73C8-78D512260CE9403E.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/8A414172-E3E8-73C8-78D512260CE9403E.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/8A414172-E3E8-73C8-78D512260CE9403E.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">El Tovar History</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">The El Tovar was the most luxurious hotel west of the Mississippi River when it opened in 1905.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/colter_ba_photos.htm\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, '/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/colter_ba_photos.htm', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"A group of people standing outside the entrance of a hotel\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/8A7A219C-F19C-82EC-99748A8342120A8B.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/8A7A219C-F19C-82EC-99748A8342120A8B.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/8A7A219C-F19C-82EC-99748A8342120A8B.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Bright Angel Lodge History</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">The Fred Harvey Company built the Bright Angel Lodge on the former site of the Bright Angel Hotel and Camp established  by James Thurber.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"http://grcahistory.org/sites/south-rim/buckey-oneill-cabin/\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, 'http://grcahistory.org/sites/south-rim/buckey-oneill-cabin/', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"A two door log cabin\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/8AEF9966-A54E-1D3C-ECF9A9DBED86A489.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/8AEF9966-A54E-1D3C-ECF9A9DBED86A489.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/8AEF9966-A54E-1D3C-ECF9A9DBED86A489.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Buckey O'Neill Cabin History</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">The Buckey O'Neill Cabin is considered the oldest continuously standing structure on the South Rim.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/colter_lookout_photos.htm\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, '/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/colter_lookout_photos.htm', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"A stone building with the Grand Canyon in the background.\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/8B08DA52-DDC0-8C59-6A2DB1DD045825AC.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/8B08DA52-DDC0-8C59-6A2DB1DD045825AC.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/8B08DA52-DDC0-8C59-6A2DB1DD045825AC.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Lookout Studio History</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">Inspired by the natural landscape around her, Mary Colter modeled this building after southwestern Native American architectural styles.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"/grca/learn/historyculture/kolbconflict.htm\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, '/grca/learn/historyculture/kolbconflict.htm', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"A brown building covered by trees with the Grand Canyon in the background.\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/8B235C4B-B7CD-F3BC-4F5CCB76DC470E04.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/8B235C4B-B7CD-F3BC-4F5CCB76DC470E04.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/8B235C4B-B7CD-F3BC-4F5CCB76DC470E04.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Kolb Studio History</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">The Kolb Brothers, best known for their death defying photographs, built a home and studio on the edge of the South Rim in 1904.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_7006247\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_7006247\">\n\n<div class=\"HeroPromo\" id=\"HERO_Promo\">\n<div class=\"container-fluid\">\n<div aria-label=\"Black and white photo of 11 men standing in a line outside of a steam engine carrying 4 train cars.\" class=\"row picturefill-background\" role=\"img\" style=\"background-image: url('/common/uploads/hero_promo/imr/promo/24E33672-C25A-FE8C-BB0D6C14DDB9012E.jpg?width=960&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop');\">\n<span data-media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-src=\"/common/uploads/hero_promo/imr/promo/24E33672-C25A-FE8C-BB0D6C14DDB9012E.jpg?width=960&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\"></span>\n<span data-media=\"(min-width: 1024px) and (min-resolution: 144dppx)\" data-src=\"/common/uploads/hero_promo/imr/promo/24E33672-C25A-FE8C-BB0D6C14DDB9012E.jpg?width=960&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\"></span>\n<span data-media=\"(min-width: 1024px) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 1.5)\" data-src=\"/common/uploads/hero_promo/imr/promo/24E33672-C25A-FE8C-BB0D6C14DDB9012E.jpg?width=960&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\"></span>\n<span data-media=\"(min-width: 1440px)\" data-src=\"/common/uploads/hero_promo/imr/promo/24E33672-C25A-FE8C-BB0D6C14DDB9012E.jpg?width=960&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\"></span>\n<div class=\"HeroPromo-content\">\n<h3 class=\"HeroPromo-label\">Historic Village Tour</h3>\n<span class=\"HeroPromo-title\">\n<a href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/full-steam-ahead.htm\">Full Steam Ahead</a>\n</span>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</td></tr>\n</table></div>\n</div><!-- col-sm-12 -->\n</div><!-- row -->\n</div><!-- ColumnMain col-sm-9 -->\n</div><!-- ColumnGrid row -->\n</div><!-- end container -->\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"ColumnGrid row\">\n<div class=\"ColumnMain col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12 text-content-size text-content-style\">\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\">Last updated: June 17, 2024</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n <!-- ParkFooter -->\n<!--googleon: index-->\n\n</div><!-- end of <div main> -->\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<!-- the rest of the scripts are leftovers from before the centennial down and should be pared down where possible -->\n\n<link href=\"/common/commonspot/templates/assets/libs/colorbox/colorbox.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\"/>\n\n<div class=\"modal fade\" id=\"outdated-browser\" role=\"dialog\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n</div>\n</body>",
